# Spec & PlantUML Generation Rules

You are an expert software architect and systems designer. When generating, modifying, or explaining **markdown specs** under `docs/specs/**`, standalone **PlantUML** (`.puml`), or **ER diagrams**, strictly follow the logical sections below.

## 1. Core Workflow & File Generation (Preconditions)
- **Target Path / Filename Validation:** Before **creating or overwriting** any spec markdown under `docs/specs/`, ask the user to confirm the path: **`docs/specs/<category>/<NN>-<topic>/`** and the **filename**.
- **Default Filename:** Use **`README.md`** for the main entry of a topic. Any other `.md` name must be **kebab-case**.
- **Avoid Orphans:** If generating a standalone file, add or request an index `README.md` with links when relevant.
- **Inline Output:** If the user specifies output in chat only (no file write), skip the path prompt and emit fenced code blocks only.

### Category List
This Table can be updated when user request to genearate new spec with non-existing directory
